WEBVTT

1
00:01:48,228 --> 00:01:49,377
You're special.

2
00:01:50,708 --> 00:01:54,337
<i>You have a very special purpose in life.</i>

3
00:01:56,468 --> 00:01:57,742
You've been chosen.

4
00:02:08,828 --> 00:02:11,058
The Island awaits you.

5
00:02:59,948 --> 00:03:01,825
I'm fine, I'm fine, I'm fine.

6
00:03:28,988 --> 00:03:30,785
<i>Good morning, Tower One.</i>

7
00:03:30,948 --> 00:03:34,145
<i>Exterior contamination index</i>
<i>is 85 percent.</i>

8
00:03:34,308 --> 00:03:35,661
<i>Sunny and mild.</i>

9
00:03:46,548 --> 00:03:48,300
Hey, I'm missing a left shoe.

10
00:03:52,108 --> 00:03:55,418
<i>And when you get a chance,</i>
<i>I'd like another color.</i>

11
00:04:05,068 --> 00:04:07,423
- Morning.
- Morning.

12
00:04:15,108 --> 00:04:18,145
- Hey, Lincoln. How you doing?
- I'm missing a shoe.

13
00:04:28,228 --> 00:04:31,345
- Hey, you're cutting.
- Yeah.

14
00:04:31,868 --> 00:04:33,745
Thank you.

15
00:04:34,588 --> 00:04:36,340
We're full.

16
00:04:39,428 --> 00:04:43,262
<i>Good morning. July 19, 2019.</i>

17
00:04:43,428 --> 00:04:45,066
Another day in paradise.

18
00:04:58,508 --> 00:05:01,898
<i>Starkweather Two Delta,</i>
<i>your time has come.</i>

19
00:05:02,428 --> 00:05:05,147
<i>You're moving out to The Island.</i>

20
00:05:05,308 --> 00:05:06,821
<i>Starkweather Two Delta here.</i>

21
00:05:06,988 --> 00:05:10,344
<i>And as you know, the biggest dream</i>
<i>of my life just came true.</i>

22
00:05:10,508 --> 00:05:15,059
<i>I mean, I've only been with you guys for,</i>
<i>like, six months, but I won the lottery.</i>

23
00:05:15,228 --> 00:05:17,139
<i>- That's right, me.</i>
- Six months.

24
00:05:17,348 --> 00:05:21,546
<i>To go out and breathe fresh air.</i>
<i>Swim in the ocean.</i>

25
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:25,542
<i>I can 't believe I won.</i>
<i>You call me Mr. Popular, I know.</i>

26
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:28,381
<i>It's me. It's me.</i>

27
00:05:28,548 --> 00:05:31,506
<i>You guys know I'm not like this,</i>
<i>but this is just amazing.</i>

28
00:05:33,628 --> 00:05:36,620
<i>I'm going to The Island!</i>
<i>We're gonna have so much fun!</i>

29
00:05:36,788 --> 00:05:39,939
<i>But I need to see you guys out there.</i>
<i>You can do it. I won!</i>

30
00:05:40,108 --> 00:05:41,427
<i>That was this week's winner...</i>

31
00:05:41,588 --> 00:05:43,863
We got a disturbance on elevator 12,
plaza level.

32
00:05:44,068 --> 00:05:47,504
<i>- Just moments before his final</i>
<i>departure to The Island...</i>

33
00:05:47,988 --> 00:05:50,502
<i>... nature's last remaining</i>
<i>pathogen-free zone.</i>

34
00:05:50,868 --> 00:05:52,938
Lucky guy, huh? Don't you think?

35
00:05:53,108 --> 00:05:56,578
<i>The next lottery is tonight.</i>

36
00:05:57,188 --> 00:06:00,624
"The next lottery is tonight."

37
00:06:02,868 --> 00:06:05,428
- How long have you been here?
- Two years.

38
00:06:06,788 --> 00:06:08,938
- What about you?
- Three.

39
00:06:09,148 --> 00:06:11,139
Three. I've been here seven.

40
00:06:11,308 --> 00:06:15,062
If I do the math, that makes me
the biggest lottery loser in the room.

41
00:06:16,908 --> 00:06:18,978
I'm such a loser.

42
00:06:47,988 --> 00:06:49,819
Sir.

43
00:06:50,228 --> 00:06:51,946
Yeah, you.

44
00:06:54,108 --> 00:06:55,382
Swipe.

45
00:06:56,988 --> 00:07:00,219
Gandu Three Echo. You've been flagged
for public disturbance before.

46
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:03,188
Yes, I had a very small
emotional outburst, sir.

47
00:07:03,348 --> 00:07:06,499
- Safe to say it's over?
- Yes, very safe.

48
00:07:06,788 --> 00:07:08,221
I'm feeling much better.

49
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:10,146
- Then have a pleasant day.
- You too.

50
00:07:10,348 --> 00:07:13,101
You both have a pleasant day too.

51
00:07:34,588 --> 00:07:35,816
Stretch.

52
00:07:37,668 --> 00:07:38,783
One more breath in.

53
00:07:58,988 --> 00:08:00,501
- Listen.
- I tried to do better.

54
00:08:01,748 --> 00:08:06,264
<i>Remember, be polite,</i>
<i>pleasant and peaceful.</i>

55
00:08:06,468 --> 00:08:09,665
<i>A healthy person is a happy person.</i>

56
00:08:16,588 --> 00:08:20,183
Lincoln Six Echo, choices are fruit,
oatmeal and any type of bran.

57
00:08:20,828 --> 00:08:22,307
No bacon today?

58
00:08:22,468 --> 00:08:24,424
You got a nutrition flag.
Means no bacon.

59
00:08:24,588 --> 00:08:27,978
Then I'll have two eggs, over easy,
not too runny, and a side of sausages.

60
00:08:28,148 --> 00:08:30,537
Maybe some French toast
and a little powdered sugar.

61
00:08:31,468 --> 00:08:34,665
You ain't cute and I got no time
for your lip, Six Echo.

62
00:08:35,268 --> 00:08:37,941
- Now, what's it gonna be?
- Move it.

63
00:08:41,068 --> 00:08:43,024
Surprise me.

64
00:08:47,508 --> 00:08:49,499
Surprise.

65
00:08:50,148 --> 00:08:52,503
Yummy. Next.

66
00:09:04,068 --> 00:09:06,457
Watch and learn.

67
00:09:08,108 --> 00:09:09,382
Next.

68
00:09:09,548 --> 00:09:11,379
Jordan Two Delta.

69
00:09:11,548 --> 00:09:13,300
- Hi, honey.
- Hi.

70
00:09:13,468 --> 00:09:16,824
Choices are powdered eggs,
dried fruit and yogurt.

71
00:09:16,988 --> 00:09:19,548
- Eggs, please.
- Okay.

72
00:09:20,988 --> 00:09:23,548
So where were you the other day?
We missed you.

73
00:09:24,308 --> 00:09:27,106
That's nice of you to say, sweetheart.

74
00:09:27,948 --> 00:09:29,347
Get you anything else?

75
00:09:30,228 --> 00:09:31,547
Maybe a little bacon.

76
00:09:32,268 --> 00:09:35,180
- No, it says I shouldn't.
- Go ahead.

77
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,744
Four... Five pieces, please.

78
00:09:39,428 --> 00:09:40,577
Thank you.

79
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:50,222
- I softened her up for you.
- No doubt.

80
00:09:50,388 --> 00:09:51,741
Back on your diet, huh?

81
00:09:51,948 --> 00:09:53,222
You kidding? I love this.

82
00:09:53,428 --> 00:09:55,817
Better eat up.
You'll need your strength tonight.

83
00:09:55,988 --> 00:09:59,219
- Is that a challenge?
- I promise I'll go easy on you.

84
00:10:01,708 --> 00:10:04,825
Please separate. Find your seats now.

85
00:10:07,668 --> 00:10:10,023
"'Who wants Sally? ' said Dick.

86
00:10:10,188 --> 00:10:12,304
'I do,' said Jane.

87
00:10:12,468 --> 00:10:15,107
'I cannot find Sally.

88
00:10:15,268 --> 00:10:19,500
Get up, Dick.
Get up and help me find Sally.'

89
00:10:20,268 --> 00:10:22,020
'Ls Sally here? '"

90
00:10:34,148 --> 00:10:36,378
Dr. Merrick will see you now.

91
00:10:40,988 --> 00:10:43,866
What did you do wrong this time,
tough guy?

92
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:48,780
Sir?

93
00:10:49,108 --> 00:10:50,700
You wanted to see me?

94
00:10:50,868 --> 00:10:53,541
Yes. Please.

95
00:11:01,788 --> 00:11:03,301
Please sit down.

96
00:11:04,748 --> 00:11:07,023
So how is Lincoln Six Echo today?

97
00:11:07,188 --> 00:11:09,258
Not so good, I guess.

98
00:11:09,868 --> 00:11:11,620
Why do you say that?

99
00:11:11,788 --> 00:11:14,302
Well, if I'm here,
it means I'm not so good.

100
00:11:14,668 --> 00:11:17,387
That's a rather negative association.

101
00:11:17,628 --> 00:11:21,587
My only job is to see that you're happy,
that things are okay with you.

102
00:11:21,828 --> 00:11:23,147
Right.

103
00:11:26,508 --> 00:11:29,147
Your file shows that you've been
interacting regularly...

104
00:11:29,308 --> 00:11:30,582
...with Jordan Two Delta.

105
00:11:30,908 --> 00:11:32,580
There's no law against friendship.

106
00:11:32,748 --> 00:11:38,698
No, we encourage it, but obviously,
proximity could become a concern.

107
00:11:38,908 --> 00:11:40,626
I know the rules of proximity.

108
00:11:42,988 --> 00:11:45,582
You've been doing quite well
in most other areas.

109
00:11:45,748 --> 00:11:48,421
Proficient at work,
exercising rigorously.

110
00:11:48,588 --> 00:11:51,898
But screening has picked up
some trace levels...

111
00:11:52,108 --> 00:11:55,896
...changes in your metabolism,
and you've been having nightmares.

112
00:11:56,428 --> 00:11:58,658
Are you saying there's something
wrong with me?

113
00:11:59,188 --> 00:12:01,418
Why don't you tell me
about your dream.

114
00:12:02,188 --> 00:12:06,181
Well, it's the same dream every time.
I'm on a boat, headed to The Island.

115
00:12:06,348 --> 00:12:09,306
A boat? What kind of boat?

116
00:12:10,788 --> 00:12:12,062
A nice boat.

117
00:12:12,308 --> 00:12:13,627
Draw it for me, would you?

118
00:12:19,028 --> 00:12:22,418
So you're heading toward The Island.

119
00:12:22,588 --> 00:12:24,260
What happens then?

120
00:12:24,428 --> 00:12:25,747
I drown.

121
00:12:25,988 --> 00:12:27,501
Really?

122
00:12:28,068 --> 00:12:29,421
Why do you think that is?

123
00:12:29,588 --> 00:12:31,340
I don't know. You tell me.

124
00:12:31,508 --> 00:12:33,942
- Are you afraid of winning?
- Why would I be afraid?

125
00:12:34,108 --> 00:12:35,666
You tell me.

126
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:42,823
What's troubling you, Lincoln?

127
00:12:44,948 --> 00:12:46,540
Well, it's...

128
00:12:46,788 --> 00:12:48,506
It's just...

129
00:12:49,588 --> 00:12:51,818
All right. Tuesday night is tofu night...

130
00:12:51,988 --> 00:12:55,537
...and I'm asking myself, "Who decided
that everyone here likes tofu?"

131
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:57,346
And what is tofu, anyway?

132
00:12:57,988 --> 00:12:59,307
And why can't I have bacon?

133
00:12:59,468 --> 00:13:02,665
I line up every morning and I'm not
allowed bacon for my breakfast.

134
00:13:03,468 --> 00:13:05,777
And tell me...
Let's talk about all the white.

135
00:13:05,948 --> 00:13:07,700
Why is everyone
always wearing white?

136
00:13:07,908 --> 00:13:09,307
It's impossible to keep clean.

137
00:13:09,468 --> 00:13:12,301
I always get the gray stripe.
I never get any color.

138
00:13:12,508 --> 00:13:15,466
And I hand it in to be cleaned,
and someone cleans it...

139
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:17,903
...and folds it neatly back in my drawer,
but who?

140
00:13:18,108 --> 00:13:20,258
Who is that person? I don't know.

141
00:13:20,988 --> 00:13:25,220
I just... I wanna know answers,
and I wish that there was more.

142
00:13:26,588 --> 00:13:27,987
More?

143
00:13:28,148 --> 00:13:32,221
Yeah. More than just waiting
to go to The Island.

144
00:13:35,188 --> 00:13:36,701
Lincoln...

145
00:13:37,588 --> 00:13:40,386
...it's your nature to question things.

146
00:13:40,548 --> 00:13:43,142
But don't you realize
how lucky you are?

147
00:13:43,348 --> 00:13:45,020
That you survived the contamination.

148
00:13:45,188 --> 00:13:48,942
That nature has left you
a Garden of Eden to repopulate.

149
00:13:49,108 --> 00:13:52,020
That, Lincoln, is your purpose.

150
00:13:56,108 --> 00:13:59,783
Right. And you?
Aren't you going to The Island too?

151
00:14:00,308 --> 00:14:01,821
No.

152
00:14:02,348 --> 00:14:07,468
My responsibility is to make sure
this facility continues to operate.

153
00:14:07,628 --> 00:14:12,748
That's why people like me,
my staff and supervisors, we...

154
00:14:13,268 --> 00:14:15,224
We can't win the lottery.

155
00:14:18,508 --> 00:14:20,544
Let me see that.

156
00:14:22,508 --> 00:14:24,146
You draw well.

157
00:14:24,308 --> 00:14:25,536
<i>"Renovatio."</i>

158
00:14:25,748 --> 00:14:29,058
- What does that mean?
- I don't know. It's always in my dream.

159
00:14:31,668 --> 00:14:33,659
I'd like to run some tests
on you, Lincoln.

160
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:38,621
- What sort of tests?
- Nice tests.

161
00:14:39,348 --> 00:14:40,497
Come with me.

162
00:14:47,588 --> 00:14:49,146
Take a seat.

163
00:14:54,028 --> 00:14:57,259
Okay, let's get you comfortable.
Swing back.

164
00:15:02,068 --> 00:15:05,299
- I thought these were nice tests.
- It's a synaptic brain scan.

165
00:15:05,468 --> 00:15:07,299
Totally harmless.

166
00:15:07,708 --> 00:15:10,176
Don't worry, it's painless.

167
00:15:30,468 --> 00:15:31,867
- It hurts.
- Not really.

168
00:15:32,068 --> 00:15:33,581
- Yeah, it does!
- No, it doesn't.

169
00:15:33,788 --> 00:15:35,938
Yeah, it really, really does!

170
00:15:41,068 --> 00:15:43,866
The microsensors will move along
your optic nerve.

171
00:15:44,428 --> 00:15:47,340
They'll be uploading readings to us
over the next 24 hours...

172
00:15:47,508 --> 00:15:49,942
...after which you'll pass them
through your urine.

173
00:15:50,108 --> 00:15:52,224
Now, that might hurt.

174
00:16:02,868 --> 00:16:04,506
Six Echo, you're late.

175
00:16:19,148 --> 00:16:21,503
- Jones, you ever get bored doing this?
- Doing what?

176
00:16:21,668 --> 00:16:23,545
- This.
- I never really thought about it.

177
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:25,346
- I think about it a lot.
- About what?

178
00:16:25,548 --> 00:16:28,142
This boring job.
What are we doing here, anyway?

179
00:16:28,308 --> 00:16:29,980
We're feeding the nutrient lines.

180
00:16:30,148 --> 00:16:32,708
We eat food,
food's gotta have vitamins, right?

181
00:16:32,868 --> 00:16:35,985
- It's good for us.
- You don't ever wonder about anything?

182
00:16:36,188 --> 00:16:38,418
Where do these tubes go?

183
00:16:40,228 --> 00:16:43,982
They start there.
And they go... right there.

184
00:16:45,348 --> 00:16:47,816
Hey, did you get a look
at the new guy?

185
00:16:48,148 --> 00:16:50,059
Seven Foxtrot.

186
00:16:50,228 --> 00:16:51,741
They found another survivor.

187
00:16:52,228 --> 00:16:55,265
- They keep finding them.
- He'll probably win the lottery tomorrow.

188
00:16:55,428 --> 00:16:57,384
Straight down, in the hole.

189
00:16:57,548 --> 00:16:59,584
There you go, you try it.
Straight down.

190
00:16:59,748 --> 00:17:01,864
- In...
- In the hole.

191
00:17:02,028 --> 00:17:05,703
In the hole. No, no. No. No.
Put it down.

192
00:17:05,868 --> 00:17:08,701
Did we look that stupid when
we went through decontamination?

193
00:17:08,908 --> 00:17:13,186
Hey, Mr. Man-With-All-the-Questions,
let me ask you this.

194
00:17:14,508 --> 00:17:17,181
- Lottery's supposed to be random, right?
- Right.

195
00:17:17,508 --> 00:17:20,341
What if it's not? What if it's rigged?

196
00:17:20,508 --> 00:17:22,021
Rigged?

197
00:17:22,948 --> 00:17:24,745
I've been working on this. Here.

198
00:17:25,308 --> 00:17:26,707
Take a look at that.

199
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:30,427
It charts the last 20 people
that won a spot on The Island.

200
00:17:30,588 --> 00:17:33,625
Excluding, of course, the women,
picked to be breeders.

201
00:17:33,788 --> 00:17:36,382
- What is this?
- I took the first letter in each name.

202
00:17:36,788 --> 00:17:39,621
I assigned it a point value
based on its alphabet position.

203
00:17:39,788 --> 00:17:41,858
Like the last, Starkweather,
S equals 15.

204
00:17:42,068 --> 00:17:45,185
Q equals 15, S equals 19.
Do you see what I'm saying?

205
00:17:45,348 --> 00:17:47,259
- No.
- Maybe if you would listen to me.

206
00:17:47,428 --> 00:17:49,066
I'm trying to tell you.

207
00:17:49,228 --> 00:17:52,061
You string the numbers together.
You divide it by the amount...

208
00:17:52,228 --> 00:17:55,698
You multiply it by the amount...
You divide it by the amount of peop...

209
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:57,626
Divide by the amount
of people here.

210
00:17:57,828 --> 00:18:01,218
Which is 25... A thousand plus 5... 2500.
You know what that spells?

211
00:18:01,908 --> 00:18:03,739
J-O-N-E-S.

212
00:18:04,828 --> 00:18:07,262
- I'm winning the lottery tonight.
- Did you pack?

213
00:18:08,828 --> 00:18:10,102
- No.
- Gentlemen...

214
00:18:11,308 --> 00:18:13,503
...I'm gonna go mess with Foxtrot.

215
00:18:13,668 --> 00:18:15,659
There you go. Straight...

216
00:18:15,828 --> 00:18:18,865
Straight down, in the hole.
There you go.

217
00:18:22,188 --> 00:18:23,701
- He had something on his...
- Go.

218
00:18:28,988 --> 00:18:30,546
Lima! Are you okay?

219
00:18:30,708 --> 00:18:34,064
Code 15! We need med-techs
down here, stat! Lima One Alpha.

220
00:18:34,228 --> 00:18:35,820
Just give her some air, okay?

221
00:18:36,108 --> 00:18:38,417
You're gonna be okay.
Just relax and breathe.

222
00:18:38,628 --> 00:18:42,177
Can I get a wheelchair down here,
please? It's for Lima One Alpha.

223
00:18:42,828 --> 00:18:44,466
I think it's time.

224
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:49,745
Lima. You're going to The Island.

225
00:18:49,948 --> 00:18:52,667
- We're going.
- Oh, you're so lucky.

226
00:18:52,868 --> 00:18:54,540
I hope I see you soon.

227
00:18:57,228 --> 00:18:58,741
Everyone, please follow her out.

228
00:18:58,948 --> 00:19:01,587
Quickly and carefully.
Watch the glass.

229
00:19:01,988 --> 00:19:04,183
- Good luck, Lima.
- Thank you.

230
00:19:08,148 --> 00:19:10,423
That's fair. That's real fair.

231
00:19:10,788 --> 00:19:13,780
Ladies, push back, please.
Gentlemen, thank you.

232
00:19:17,548 --> 00:19:19,664
Everyone, back to work.

233
00:19:19,988 --> 00:19:22,104
That is so not fair!

234
00:19:22,548 --> 00:19:26,302
Oh, man, I hate this jealousy thing.
It's giving me heart palpitations.

235
00:19:26,468 --> 00:19:28,186
Tech Services.

236
00:19:28,628 --> 00:19:30,141
Computer's down again.

237
00:19:31,228 --> 00:19:33,059
I'm down.
Computer guy's in Sector Six.

238
00:19:33,228 --> 00:19:35,378
I have to deal with this mess.
Take my Tri-key.

239
00:19:35,548 --> 00:19:38,346
- Contamination kit. Hurry back.
- Absolutely.

240
00:20:06,148 --> 00:20:08,708
- Hey! What are you doing?
- I'm gonna see this guy.

241
00:20:10,028 --> 00:20:13,543
Hey, we've got live wires
all over the place here.

