00:44:58,188 --> 00:44:59,985
Check over here!

490
00:45:00,188 --> 00:45:02,258
Watch your left! Watch your left!

491
00:45:03,068 --> 00:45:04,547
Run.

492
00:45:08,028 --> 00:45:09,427
Run.

493
00:45:09,628 --> 00:45:11,425
He's over here.

494
00:45:12,868 --> 00:45:17,180
<i>Very special.</i>
<i>You want to go to The Island.</i>

495
00:45:17,348 --> 00:45:19,623
There they are.

496
00:45:32,708 --> 00:45:34,858
- Lincoln!
- Come on!

497
00:45:35,028 --> 00:45:37,258
Get them! Let's go!

498
00:45:37,468 --> 00:45:40,301
- Move!
- Come on!

499
00:45:41,388 --> 00:45:43,140
Come on, come on. Damn!

500
00:45:43,908 --> 00:45:46,661
Go, go, go. Come on.

501
00:45:50,228 --> 00:45:52,423
You still think there's an Island?

502
00:46:02,748 --> 00:46:04,147
Come on.

503
00:46:28,508 --> 00:46:30,703
Come on. Come on.

504
00:46:48,068 --> 00:46:49,786
There's a door over here!

505
00:48:02,348 --> 00:48:06,944
<i>Lincoln Six Echo remains in quarantine</i>
<i>after contamination exposure.</i>

506
00:48:07,108 --> 00:48:12,023
<i>Jordan Two Delta was safely transported</i>
<i>to her new home on The Island.</i>

507
00:48:12,428 --> 00:48:15,340
Jones Three Echo, I need you
to concentrate in this lab.

508
00:48:15,548 --> 00:48:18,540
Sir, I want to focus.
I love my job. It's very interesting.

509
00:48:18,748 --> 00:48:21,626
But Lincoln Six Echo
has been contaminated...

510
00:48:21,828 --> 00:48:25,025
...and it really worries me because
he's a very good friend of mine.

511
00:48:25,188 --> 00:48:27,019
And he's my only best friend.

512
00:48:27,228 --> 00:48:29,344
He'll be fine, Three Echo.

513
00:48:29,508 --> 00:48:33,421
Sir, I have one question.
Where do all the tubes go?

514
00:48:35,988 --> 00:48:37,660
<i>The human organism.</i>

515
00:48:37,828 --> 00:48:40,581
<i>Unique in all the universe</i>
<i>in its complexity.</i>

516
00:48:40,748 --> 00:48:43,387
<i>The product of 3 billion years</i>
<i>of evolution.</i>

517
00:48:43,548 --> 00:48:46,779
<i>Prefect in every way except one.</i>

518
00:48:46,988 --> 00:48:50,344
<i>Like all machines, it wears out.</i>

519
00:48:50,868 --> 00:48:53,541
<i>For centuries, the idea of replenishing</i>
<i>the human body...</i>

520
00:48:53,748 --> 00:48:55,704
<i>... has been at the forefront</i>
<i>of science.</i>

521
00:48:55,868 --> 00:48:58,428
I think we need to turn this bad day
into a good day.

522
00:48:58,588 --> 00:49:00,977
- How?
- By selling. Sell, sell, sell.

523
00:49:01,148 --> 00:49:02,627
You start, I finish.

524
00:49:12,588 --> 00:49:14,385
Ladies and gentlemen...

525
00:49:14,548 --> 00:49:18,097
...welcome to the next generation
of science:

526
00:49:18,308 --> 00:49:20,105
The agnate.

527
00:49:20,268 --> 00:49:24,181
An organic frame engineered
directly into adulthood...

528
00:49:24,348 --> 00:49:25,861
...to match the client's age.

529
00:49:26,548 --> 00:49:29,904
You're looking at stage one
of its development.

530
00:49:30,068 --> 00:49:32,502
Within 12 months,
it will be harvest-ready...

531
00:49:32,668 --> 00:49:36,741
...providing a carrier for your baby,
a second pair of lungs, fresh skin...

532
00:49:36,908 --> 00:49:40,139
...all genetically indistinguishable
from your own.

533
00:49:40,308 --> 00:49:44,824
And in compliance
with the eugenics laws of 2015...

534
00:49:44,988 --> 00:49:49,937
...all our agnates are maintained
in a persistent vegetative state.

535
00:49:50,108 --> 00:49:52,144
They never achieve consciousness.

536
00:49:52,348 --> 00:49:54,737
They never think...

537
00:49:54,908 --> 00:49:59,379
...or suffer or feel pain,
joy, love, hate.

538
00:49:59,548 --> 00:50:02,187
It's a product, ladies and gentlemen...

539
00:50:02,348 --> 00:50:04,066
...in every way that matters.

540
00:50:05,028 --> 00:50:07,542
<i>Not human.</i>

541
00:50:11,668 --> 00:50:14,785
This is our public-relations director,
Mr. Whitman.

542
00:50:14,948 --> 00:50:17,018
He'll be happy to answer
your questions.

543
00:50:17,188 --> 00:50:19,099
Once again, thank you.
Mr. Whitman.

544
00:50:19,308 --> 00:50:23,062
I wanna talk about the smartest
investment you'll ever make.

545
00:50:23,828 --> 00:50:27,503
And I wanna tell you how you're gonna
live 60 to <i>70</i> years longer.

546
00:50:31,668 --> 00:50:34,944
Dr. Merrick, Albert Laurent,
Blackhawk Security.

547
00:50:35,108 --> 00:50:38,259
You come highly recommended by
the Defense Department, Mr. Laurent.

548
00:50:38,468 --> 00:50:41,062
Though I'm unaware
of your personal qualifications.

549
00:50:41,228 --> 00:50:43,822
My men are ex-Delta Force. SEALs.

550
00:50:43,988 --> 00:50:46,582
I was formerly with the GIGN,
French special forces.

551
00:50:46,788 --> 00:50:48,858
I understand you had
a corporate theft.

552
00:50:49,068 --> 00:50:51,343
Yes, that's what I told
the Defense Department.

553
00:50:51,508 --> 00:50:55,183
The reality is a little more complex.
That's why I require your services.

554
00:50:55,348 --> 00:50:58,226
We've had a security breach.

555
00:50:58,428 --> 00:51:01,818
You have the Defense Department
at your disposal. Why call me?

556
00:51:02,028 --> 00:51:04,542
Because their investment here
is sizable.

557
00:51:04,708 --> 00:51:07,666
One hundred and twenty billion dollars,
to be exact.

558
00:51:07,828 --> 00:51:10,501
And I can't afford for them
to reconsider.

559
00:51:10,708 --> 00:51:12,699
What you tell them
is your business, doctor.

560
00:51:12,868 --> 00:51:15,621
I am in the business of keeping
my clients' confidence.

561
00:51:16,348 --> 00:51:17,827
Good.

562
00:51:21,628 --> 00:51:24,096
Two of our products have escaped.

563
00:51:24,308 --> 00:51:26,697
Impressive, considering
they're vegetative.

564
00:51:26,868 --> 00:51:29,701
Well, after several years
of trial and error...

565
00:51:29,868 --> 00:51:31,938
...we discovered that
without consciousness...

566
00:51:32,108 --> 00:51:34,019
...without human experience, emotion...

567
00:51:34,748 --> 00:51:36,500
...without life...

568
00:51:37,308 --> 00:51:39,264
...the organs failed.

569
00:51:41,228 --> 00:51:42,820
How long have they been missing?

570
00:51:43,668 --> 00:51:45,624
Four hours and 36 minutes.

571
00:51:45,788 --> 00:51:48,382
- They're on foot?
- Yes.

572
00:51:48,548 --> 00:51:52,097
Wade, 1.2 miles an hour,
five-mile perimeter.

573
00:51:52,308 --> 00:51:54,264
Stand by for suspect description.

574
00:51:54,468 --> 00:51:56,618
- We're on it.
- Follow me.

575
00:52:13,108 --> 00:52:16,225
- Come on. We gotta keep going.
- I have to stop. I can't run anymore.

576
00:52:16,388 --> 00:52:17,821
- You gotta try. Come on.
- Where?

577
00:52:18,028 --> 00:52:20,098
- Anywhere but here.
- But there's nothing.

578
00:52:20,268 --> 00:52:22,702
Everything's dead, Lincoln.

579
00:52:28,348 --> 00:52:30,418
What if we are contaminated?

580
00:52:31,188 --> 00:52:32,940
Then we'd be dead.

581
00:52:33,908 --> 00:52:37,264
There's no contamination.
It was a lie.

582
00:52:47,228 --> 00:52:48,502
What is it?

583
00:52:48,668 --> 00:52:51,580
I don't know. But it's alive.

584
00:52:56,268 --> 00:52:58,941
Come on. It's mean, whatever it is.

585
00:52:59,108 --> 00:53:00,382
Let's rest in here.

586
00:53:00,548 --> 00:53:04,177
Jordan Two Delta sponsor, Sarah Jordan,
is in a coma after a car accident.

587
00:53:04,348 --> 00:53:06,543
She's in need of multiple
organ transplants.

588
00:53:06,708 --> 00:53:07,777
How long does she have?

589
00:53:08,188 --> 00:53:10,224
Forty-eight hours.
Three days, maximum.

590
00:53:10,548 --> 00:53:11,947
Tell me about Six Echo.

591
00:53:12,148 --> 00:53:15,345
Well, he was really the first one
to question his environment...

592
00:53:15,508 --> 00:53:16,827
...his whole existence here.

593
00:53:17,908 --> 00:53:21,025
The last few months, he began
demonstrating unstable behavior...

594
00:53:21,188 --> 00:53:23,702
...and I can't account for it.

595
00:53:23,908 --> 00:53:26,103
I'm waiting on the result
of his synaptic scan.

596
00:53:26,268 --> 00:53:27,986
What do they know
about the outside world?

597
00:53:28,828 --> 00:53:30,466
Very little.

598
00:53:30,628 --> 00:53:33,540
We control them with the memory
of a shared event.

599
00:53:33,708 --> 00:53:35,141
A global contamination.

600
00:53:35,348 --> 00:53:37,737
It keeps them fearful of going outside.

601
00:53:37,948 --> 00:53:41,782
The Island is the one thing
that gives them hope.

602
00:53:42,308 --> 00:53:44,344
Gives them purpose.

603
00:53:44,948 --> 00:53:47,018
Everything we expose them to...

604
00:53:47,188 --> 00:53:50,498
...their programs, their cartoons,
books, the games they play...

605
00:53:50,708 --> 00:53:54,018
...are designed to manage aggression
and reinforce simple social skills.

606
00:53:54,588 --> 00:53:56,544
<i>To avoid obvious complications...</i>

607
00:53:56,708 --> 00:53:59,222
<i>... they aren 't imprinted</i>
<i>with an awareness of sex.</i>

608
00:53:59,388 --> 00:54:02,380
<i>We find it simpler to eliminate</i>
<i>the drive altogether.</i>

609
00:54:03,108 --> 00:54:05,497
In a very real sense...

610
00:54:06,268 --> 00:54:08,020
...they're like children.

611
00:54:08,188 --> 00:54:10,622
Educated to the level of a 15-year-old.

612
00:54:27,308 --> 00:54:30,220
- What was that?
- I don't know.

613
00:54:31,868 --> 00:54:33,779
But I want one.

614
00:54:47,548 --> 00:54:49,027
Look!

615
00:54:49,948 --> 00:54:53,065
Route 39. Route 39.

616
00:54:53,228 --> 00:54:54,786
Come on.

617
00:54:55,468 --> 00:54:57,663
I got it from a friend.

618
00:55:21,228 --> 00:55:23,105
I think that's it.

619
00:55:53,468 --> 00:55:54,742
What's up?

620
00:55:54,908 --> 00:55:56,899
Yeah, do you know
a guy named McCord?

621
00:55:58,588 --> 00:56:00,579
Yeah, we know that tool.
Who's asking?

622
00:56:01,628 --> 00:56:05,098
- I am.
- And you would be who?

623
00:56:05,348 --> 00:56:08,146
- Lincoln Six Echo.
- Jordan Two Delta.

624
00:56:09,548 --> 00:56:11,106
Right.

625
00:56:11,788 --> 00:56:13,938
Y'all some of those
desert UFO freaks?

626
00:56:14,148 --> 00:56:17,265
- U...? What? No. I don't think so, no.
- No.

627
00:56:17,428 --> 00:56:19,384
- McCord?
- Well, lucky day, Captain Kirk.

628
00:56:19,548 --> 00:56:21,664
- He's in the can.
- He's in a can?

629
00:56:21,868 --> 00:56:23,506
Taking a dump.

630
00:56:23,708 --> 00:56:25,744
A dump? Taking it where?

631
00:56:27,428 --> 00:56:29,658
Tell you what,
you're fixing to get on my nerves.

632
00:56:29,828 --> 00:56:32,979
- It's the first door on the right.
- Thank you.

633
00:56:33,148 --> 00:56:35,742
I have to go.
He's taking a dump in a can.

634
00:56:35,948 --> 00:56:38,746
- Something to drink? Jack?
- Yes, please.

635
00:56:39,108 --> 00:56:40,700
Straight up?

636
00:56:51,908 --> 00:56:53,466
That is bitchen.

637
00:56:55,788 --> 00:56:57,380
So this is Sector Five?

638
00:56:57,588 --> 00:56:59,624
Hey! You son of a bitch!

639
00:57:01,508 --> 00:57:03,146
You knew!

640
00:57:03,308 --> 00:57:06,584
- How the hell did you get out?
- Why? Why do they lie to us? Tell me!

641
00:57:06,748 --> 00:57:09,262
- They'll be looking for you.
- Tell me what's going on!

642
00:57:09,468 --> 00:57:13,302
What's going on is if anybody sees us
together, both of us are gonna be dead.

643
00:57:13,708 --> 00:57:16,097
So will you just take your hands off me?
Let me...

644
00:57:16,908 --> 00:57:20,298
Let me pull my pants up.
I'll take you back to my place...

645
00:57:20,748 --> 00:57:22,067
...so we can be alone, okay?

646
00:57:25,228 --> 00:57:28,265
- Ed.
- Mac.

647
00:57:29,348 --> 00:57:31,464
Give you boys a minute?

648
00:57:33,548 --> 00:57:35,300
What? This isn't what it looks like.

649
00:57:37,708 --> 00:57:39,505
Sure. Sure.

650
00:57:39,708 --> 00:57:43,940
Get out of here, you stupid...
Will you stop?

651
00:57:45,068 --> 00:57:48,185
You can't just bust in on a guy like that.
That's really rude.

652
00:57:49,668 --> 00:57:51,818
She doesn't understand licking.

653
00:57:51,988 --> 00:57:54,627
What are you, a knucklehead?
You brought another with you?

654
00:57:54,828 --> 00:57:56,227
Excuse me. Listen, will you...?

655
00:57:56,388 --> 00:57:58,822
Hey, back off, Joe, okay?
Don't push me!

656
00:57:58,988 --> 00:58:01,627
No, that's no good.
Put it on my tab. We gotta go.

657
00:58:01,788 --> 00:58:03,699
Friends of mine.
They're from out of town.

658
00:58:03,868 --> 00:58:05,381
- Let's go.
- Give me your number.

659
00:58:05,548 --> 00:58:08,824
- Two Delta.
- Hey. Don't test me.

660
00:58:08,988 --> 00:58:10,501
Don't.

661
00:58:21,908 --> 00:58:24,297
Well, this is nice.

662
00:58:27,548 --> 00:58:30,142
Mac doesn't talk much
about his work at the Institute.

663
00:58:30,308 --> 00:58:32,378
Do y'all work with him?

664
00:58:33,668 --> 00:58:36,626
Saving lives and all
must be real rewarding.

665
00:58:36,788 --> 00:58:38,779
Some fancy tracksuits.

666
00:58:39,268 --> 00:58:43,307
Y'all exercise out in this heat, you'll get
yourself some nasty heat stroke.

667
00:58:43,468 --> 00:58:44,742
Oh, Mac.

668
00:58:44,948 --> 00:58:48,497
Look, they got matching bracelets.
We should do that, honey.

669
00:58:48,708 --> 00:58:50,027
Suzie.

670
00:58:51,268 --> 00:58:53,736
Do you remember the talk
we had about all the talk?

671
00:58:55,468 --> 00:58:56,742
Yeah.

672
00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:59,422
Would you run down to Red's
and pick up a sixer of Bud?

673
00:58:59,628 --> 00:59:02,700
- We gotta talk shop.
- Okay, baby.

674
00:59:02,908 --> 00:59:04,182
Just making friends.

675
00:59:04,388 --> 00:59:06,219
- I know. Good. Just...
- Bye.

676
00:59:12,548 --> 00:59:13,742
Why do they lie, Mac?

677
00:59:14,188 --> 00:59:16,702
Why do they lie to us? Tell me.

678
00:59:19,828 --> 00:59:21,784
To keep you from knowing
what you are.

679
00:59:22,788 --> 00:59:26,098
- What we are?
- What are we?

680
00:59:26,548 --> 00:59:29,984
Man, why do I gotta be the guy that
tells the kids there's no Santa Claus?

681
00:59:34,242 --> 00:59:36,517
Okay, look. You're...

682
00:59:38,722 --> 00:59:40,758
Well, you're not like me.

683
00:59:43,002 --> 00:59:45,516
I mean, you're not human.

684
00:59:47,082 --> 00:59:51,155
I mean, you're human, but you're just...
You're not real.

685
00:59:51,602 --> 00:59:53,194
You're not like a real person.

686
00:59:53,522 --> 00:59:55,114
Like me.

687
00:59:57,922 --> 00:59:59,878
You're clones.

688
01:00:02,162 --> 01:00:05,632
You're copies of people
out here in the world.

689
01:00:06,322 --> 01:00:07,596
- What?
- Clones?

690
01:00:07,762 --> 01:00:09,878
- What? Why?
- What are you talking about?

691
01:00:10,082 --> 01:00:12,721
Some hag trophy wife
needs new skin for a face-lift...

692
01:00:12,922 --> 01:00:17,074
...or one of them gets sick and they
need a new part, they take it from you.

693
01:00:18,962 --> 01:00:21,874
But I have a mother. I remember her.

694
01:00:22,082 --> 01:00:24,038
- Yeah, I know.
- I grew up on a farm.

695
01:00:24,242 --> 01:00:27,678
- I have a little dog and I had a bike.
- And a bike. Right.

696
01:00:27,842 --> 01:00:30,959
It was a pink Flexi-Flyer
with little tassels on the handlebars...

697
01:00:31,162 --> 01:00:33,153
...and you rode it
to your grandma's house.

698
01:00:33,362 --> 01:00:36,354
You ring a bell. She came out,
served you cookies on a hot plate.

699
01:00:36,722 --> 01:00:40,510
- Yeah.
- No. Memory imprints.

700
01:00:41,562 --> 01:00:45,157
I seen them. My buddy is a programmer
at the Institute. He showed me.

701
01:00:45,322 --> 01:00:48,439
There's only, like, 12 stories.
They change around little details.

702
01:00:48,642 --> 01:00:50,633
But they're all pretty much the same.

703
01:00:50,842 --> 01:00:56,075
The life you think you had
before the "contamination"?

704
01:00:56,242 --> 01:00:58,039
It never happened.

705
01:00:59,642 --> 01:01:02,998
Come on, don't look at me like that.
At least you had a bike.

706
01:01:03,162 --> 01:01:07,075
Wanna trade your rosy memory implants
for my shitty childhood? Be my guest.

707
01:01:07,482 --> 01:01:08,597
How long?

708
01:01:09,802 --> 01:01:11,235
How long have we been alive?

709
01:01:12,642 --> 01:01:15,202
You're Echo generation, so you're 3.

710
01:01:17,002 --> 01:01:18,276
Delta means you're 4.

711
01:01:20,962 --> 01:01:22,077
Three?

712
01:01:22,242 --> 01:01:25,951
The whole reason you exist is because
everyone wants to live forever.

713
01:01:26,122 --> 01:01:27,635
It's the new American dream.

714
01:01:27,802 --> 01:01:31,078
There's people out there that are
rich enough to pay anything for it.

715
01:01:31,282 --> 01:01:34,354
Don't people care that they kill us?
That they take parts from us?

716
01:01:34,522 --> 01:01:38,640
They don't know. They think you're
vegetables simmering in a jelly sac.

717
01:01:39,402 --> 01:01:43,315
Why do you think Merrick has you stuck
in an old military bunker below ground?

718
01:01:43,482 --> 01:01:46,713
He doesn't want anyone knowing
the truth. Especially not your sponsors.

719
01:01:47,202 --> 01:01:50,478
- Sponsors?
- The people that had you made.

720
01:01:50,642 --> 01:01:52,598
They, like, own you.

721
01:01:55,042 --> 01:02:00,162
But why doesn't Merrick want
our owners to know that we're alive?

722
01:02:00,642 --> 01:02:04,601
Just because people eat the burger
doesn't mean they wanna meet the cow.

723
01:02:05,842 --> 01:02:07,116
Besides...

724
01:02:07,282 --> 01:02:11,673
...do you know how many laws Merrick's
breaking to have you two hatched?

725
01:02:13,522 --> 01:02:15,433
Your sponsors can't have
any part of that.

726
01:02:15,602 --> 01:02:18,070
They're, like, high society.
Rich and famous.

727
01:02:18,242 --> 01:02:20,358
If they knew,
Merrick would be out of business.

728
01:02:20,522 --> 01:02:23,355
We have to find our sponsors
and tell them the real truth.

729
01:02:23,562 --> 01:02:24,836
- What? No.
